<item>
            <title>[PIG-2273] Pig.compileFromFile in embedded python fails when pig script starts with a comment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2273</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using embedded Pig inside python, Pig.compileFromFile fails when the referenced pig file starts with a comment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When you start the referenced pig file with a comment, you get no plan back and hence cannot successfully execute the job.  When you start the same script without a comment, you get a plan and can execute the script successfully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Strangely, this issue does not appear when using Pig.compile to compile directly from a string.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12522465">PIG-2273</key>
            <summary>Pig.compileFromFile in embedded python fails when pig script starts with a comment</summary>
